Review control description: (i) The aggregate long position of all FPIs, each of whom has a net long position
in any IRF instrument, shall not exceed ₹5,000 crore, aggregated across all
IRF instruments;

Review control description: The wholly owned subsidiary / joint venture of a market-maker incorporated
in India may undertake such transactions provided the wholly owned
subsidiary / joint venture is a banking entity;

Review control description: (ii) A market-maker shall have the option of not reporting transactions where
the gross notional of the contract does not exceed US $ 1 million or
equivalent;
